    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-07T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-07T03:00:00-05:00" n="368"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/11–745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-07T10:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 7, 1945—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>657. Re my 656, November 6.<note n="96" xml:id="d368fn1">Not printed; it reported
                        the return from Moscow of Georgi Dimitrov to Sofia (874.00/11–645).</note>
                    Three outstanding points made yesterday afternoon by Dimitrov in his vigorous,
                    fist-pounding speech <pb facs="0379" n="367" xml:id="pg_367"/> in support of
                    present order in Bulgaria were: first, elections shall be held November 18;
                    second, they shall be held by present government led by Kimon Georgiev; third,
                    any changes in government, any reconstruction that may be considered necessary
                    will be accomplished later by Nation[al] Assembly, not now by pressure of
                    opposition.</p>
                <p>Further details will follow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Barnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
